profile_positions.description:
The R4CR program aims at strengthening the capacity of Civil Society Organizations (CSOs) on Sint Maarten in their reconstruction and rehabilitation efforts after hurricane Irma hit the island severely in 2017. Under R4CR, CSOs will be invited to submit proposals for projects benefitting local communities. In addition, CSOs will receive support in managing and monitoring their projects and will be offered a platform for exchange and cooperation with other organizations.

As R4CR team leader, based on Sint Maarten, the following main duties have been identified:
- Overall management of the R4CR program;
 - Lead, supervise and coordinate all tasks and responsibilities of the Project Implementation Unit (PIU) on Sint Maarten;
 - Ensure solid communication structures with all project stakeholders including the World Bank, the National Recovery Program Bureau (NRPB), the Dutch Representation Office on Sint Maarten (VNP), the Civil Society Organizations (CSOs) and the Government of Sint Maarten.
